Have you ever wanted your very own velcro house panther? Meet Onyx, a 2 year old baby girl who is looking for a home in the Milwaukee area. She is spayed, parasite protected, and will be up-to-date on vax as of next week. When I tell you this girl is sweet - it might be an understatement. She rubs herself all around me then presses her body into me like she’s giving a kitty hug. She is sadly already declawed in her front feet so she would do best in a home with a respectful cat and/or dog (she has previously lived with both). She is currently being independently fostered by me because her previous owner passed away and the owner’s family was violently allergic 😢 Won’t you help me find this girl a home for the holidays? DM me for a local meet & greet or to apply for adoption 🖤 
. . .

Moose also known as "Moosifer," "Moosey-woo," and "MooMoo" was voted most likely to perform a grand romantic gesture. Would he show up outside your window with a boombox above his head blaring Peter Gabriel? Bring you a dozen roses? Ask to meet up at the top of Empire State Building on Valentine's Day? Only time will tell. For now, this sweet, lovable lug is looking to nuzzle his way into your heart. 

This guy was surrendered to us from a home with a lot of other kitties, so he's a little shy at first. But he warms up after a few days! This guy would be happy in a home with 1-2 other lady cats or on his own. He prefers the quiet life, where he get pets in peace. He is neutered, micro-chipped, up-to-date on vaccines and parasite prevention. Currently being fostered in the Milwaukee area.

Won't you please take a chance on Moose and bring him home for the holidays 🥰 DM for an application!

EDIT: All three kittens are adopted 💓

Super sweet, personable kittens available for adoption in the Milwaukee area 🥰

Left to right is Elora Danan (F), Cheese (M), and Willie Jack (F). Peep my featured Foster stories for more about their purrsonalities. 

These babes were rescued with their mom in my neighborhood just before the first frost when they were still very smol. They are between 8 & 9 weeks old now and will be altered, given their age appropriate vax, and vetted on Jan. 4th. 

All kittens must be adopted in pairs or to a home with another young, playful cat. 

Please DM or email me at megankott(at)gmail(dot)com to apply for these fluffy angels. Or please share with folks would be interested 💓

I love making these 15 minute watercolor pet sketches. They are a great way to warm up for a full painting sesh. I just set the timer and see what happens. Pro-tips: 1.) Spend the first 5 minutes getting the sketch right, that’ll help getting the likeness correct. 2.) Don’t use too much water - you’ll spend half your allotted time waiting for things to dry. 3.) Don’t be too precious. Sometimes I have to do 2-3 of these in order to have 1 good one. Have fun!
. . .

THANK YOU!!!! We reached the 2k goal for Daisy’s dental surgery in less than 24 hours! I’m beyond honored by your outpouring of generosity for a 12 year old street kitty. She goes in for her recheck on April 6th. Hopefully she is over her nasty ear infection by then, and we can get her scheduled for her dental surgery. I will keep everyone updated on any news we get! 🥰
We raised $2136.70. With Daisy’s surgery estimated at $1815.27, mandatory bloodwork for $206, and assessment fee of 165.68 we decided anything extra from what we raised will be donated to @madisoncatproject 💖 A local cat rescue that is near and dear to my heart. This was my first live so be kind as I stumble over my words of gratitude 😅💓

UPDATE: ADOPTED 💓
Primrose, or “Prim” for short, is ready for her CATillion ball! During college she majored in purring while receiving her minor in lap snuggling. She might appear to be a wallflower at first, but this sweet lady is ready to be the belle of the ball! (She’s a little shy at first but warms up quickly.) She loves sports like the high-jump, ribbon-dancing, or feather flinging. She plays solo right now, but longs to be a part of a team. Perhaps another young, playful kitten or two want to be her teammates?

Prim would do best in a home where her adopter had the time to let her come out of her shell and introduce her to their social clique (of kitties). Prim wants to run & play & jump & purr. Sound like a good fit?

Won’t you take a chance on this tortie teen & sign her yearbook (aka set up a meet & greet)? See my featured foster stories to apply 💓

If you’ve thought about opening your heart & home up to another animal - now is the time. Shelters are full, lining the hallways with kennels to try to keep up with demand. And if you aren’t in a place to adopt another animal, consider signing up to foster. If you have an open bathroom, you have the space. And if you aren’t in a spot to do either of those maybe you can make cupcakes and have a bake sale for a local rescue, maybe you can donate old towels to the shelter, maybe you can drive animals to and from the vet clinic. There are lots of ways to help 💓💓💓

Help fix KC the Rescue Cat’s Teeth 🦷 We are trying to raise $1599.90 to help cover the cost of his dental surgery and surgery pre-check. It is unlikely he would find an adopter without this procedure. For every $5 or more donated you are entered into a raffle for one of three 15 min watercolor pet sketches (like this one!) done by me. The fundraiser will end on Friday, Dec. 1st CST. The raffle will end after we reach our goal. Any additional funds raised will go to @urbancatmke a Milwaukee TNR org. To enter follow the link in my profile or go to bit.ly/fixkcsteeth 🐾 Be sure to include your name/email to be entered. Pro tip: Set the transaction is set to private so your email isn’t public. #helpfixkcsteeth

Thank you so very much for donating to KC the kitty’s dental surgery! We were able to raise the funds in less than two days. We raised a total of $2072.17, we only needed $1599.90 for KC’s surgery & surgery pre-check, which means we were able to donate $472.27 to @urbancatmke (a Milwaukee rescue group focusing on TNR). The winners of the raffle have been a little harder to track down than I’d like but I am working on notifying them. Hint, if I’ve friended you in the last 24 hours on Venmo - there’s a good reason for it 😉 But truly. Thank you again. I am honored & humbled by this amazing rescue community we’ve created here. And of course KC thanks you too 🥰🐾 Swipe to see cute KC pics 🐈 And just to add some sugar to the mix - he will be available for adoption soon in the MKE area via our partners @raggedclawsrescue 💓
